    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="464"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">974.5301/8–1351: Despatch</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d464fn1">Drafted by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MGH1"
                            >Mattison</persName>; sent also to New York, the Arab capitals, London,
                        and Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/> No. 354</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-13">August 13,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Ref: <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> No. 200, dated
                    August 11, 1951<note n="2" xml:id="d464fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: <persName corresp="#p_AAR1">Azzam Pasha</persName>’s
                    Call re Suez Canal Restrictions</p>
                <p>Azzam <persName corresp="#p_AAR1">Pasha</persName>’s call on me, and his direct
                    intervention on the Suez Canal problem is only surprising in that it did not
                    occur before.</p>
                <p>Azzam and I have had a good relationship and he has in the past definitely
                    soft-pedaled the Suez Canal issue. His call in that connection was obviously as
                    the result of needling on the part of <persName corresp="#p_SBM1"
                        >Salaheddin</persName>.</p>
                <p>The intervention of the Arab League at the present juncture is to be deplored, as
                    it will only produce greater misunderstanding and friction if the Security
                    Council resolution is passed. The League’s well-known ability to produce
                    unpleasantness out of a least common denominator has been amply demonstrated in
                    the past and there is no reason to believe that the results will be any
                    different in the present case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
